<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="485" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="485">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="485">The holotype was deposited in the collection at the South Africa Institute for Medical Research (SAIMR). Part of the fly collection of the SAIMR was donated to the Natal Museum (now KwaZulu-Natal Museum - NMSA) in 1983. There is no collector indicated on the label, but in the publication Dr F. Zumpt is identified as the collector. There are no other specimens of this species in the collection. The condition of the specimen is fair. The head lacks both antennae and is glued to a card which is pinned below the specimen.</paragraph>
